## Migrate existing overlays in ../nixpkgs/overlays

To integrate with home.nix


## Use more fixed flake registry entries

Full doc for flake references: https://nixos.org/manual/nix/unstable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-flake.html#flake-references
Full doc for format of `registry.json`: https://nixos.org/manual/nix/unstable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-registry.html#registry-format

Example of a smart config: https://gitlab.univ-rouen.fr/sreycoyrehourcq/dotfiles/-/blob/2ef3b82d6a/flake.nix#L127
==> Using 2 main registry entries:
    - 'self' that points to its home conf' outPath itself
    - 'nixpkgs' that points to the nixpkgs input for its home conf
      (through a flake reference by 'path', automatically updated by its home config)

## Doc/Talk about registry entry `pkgs` for unstable

Run `nix registry add pkgs github:nixos/nixpkgs/nixpkgs-unstable`, so I can simply use `nix run pkgs#just` (for example) to run the latest cached version of `just`.



